186
00:11:51,400 --> 00:11:52,910
When I was young,

187
00:11:53,340 --> 00:11:54,650
I often had nightmares too.

188
00:11:55,790 --> 00:11:57,410
When I woke up scared from a nightmare,

189
00:11:58,570 --> 00:11:59,800
I didn't dare go back to sleep,

190
00:12:00,710 --> 00:12:02,120
nor did I dare light a candle.

191
00:12:03,320 --> 00:12:06,150
I'd just sit there until morning.

192
00:12:08,320 --> 00:12:10,450
Because my father didn't like weak children.

193
00:12:10,530 --> 00:12:13,750
I didn't expect you to have gone through that kind of life.

194
00:12:13,770 --> 00:12:15,530
Actually, everyone has nightmares sometimes.

195
00:12:15,830 --> 00:12:17,070
Even now, as an adult,

196
00:12:17,850 --> 00:12:21,120
I still occasionally have scary dreams.

197
00:12:21,690 --> 00:12:23,270
When I wake up from a nightmare,

198
00:12:23,490 --> 00:12:25,960
I'll light a candle and then go back to sleep.

199
00:12:27,260 --> 00:12:28,340
So,

200
00:12:29,210 --> 00:12:32,700
is it better to have someone who looks after you

201
00:12:33,870 --> 00:12:35,350
or to have no one?

202
00:12:36,070 --> 00:12:37,110
I can't tell anymore.

203
00:12:37,110 --> 00:12:39,790
When I was young, I often had nightmares too.

204
00:12:40,350 --> 00:12:41,540
But I was very poor

205
00:12:41,770 --> 00:12:43,180
and couldn't afford candles.

206
00:12:43,620 --> 00:12:45,200
So every time I had a nightmare,

207
00:12:46,370 --> 00:12:49,980
I would just lie in bed and wait for the morning light.

208
00:12:52,070 --> 00:12:53,250
Do you think

209
00:12:53,670 --> 00:12:55,260
this counts as a kind of weakness?

210
00:12:56,020 --> 00:12:57,860
This has nothing to do with weakness.

211
00:12:58,620 --> 00:13:01,390
You're just a young girl living a precarious life,

212
00:13:01,780 --> 00:13:04,830
already bearing pressures others couldn't handle.

213
00:13:05,150 --> 00:13:06,630
Having nightmares is perfectly normal.

214
00:13:09,230 --> 00:13:10,070
But

215
00:13:10,880 --> 00:13:14,100
you've managed to maintain that innocence and calmness,

216
00:13:15,280 --> 00:13:18,170
which is already a strength I can't even compare to.

217
00:13:19,330 --> 00:13:21,070
I'm not as strong as you say.

218
00:13:21,690 --> 00:13:22,790
How do I put it?

219
00:13:23,330 --> 00:13:24,680
I just think

220
00:13:25,540 --> 00:13:27,300
that if a person is always

221
00:13:27,330 --> 00:13:29,030
in a dangerous situation,

222
00:13:29,630 --> 00:13:31,020
they'll naturally

223
00:13:31,200 --> 00:13:33,040
learn how to adapt.

224
00:13:33,350 --> 00:13:34,460
That's not necessarily true.

225
00:13:35,470 --> 00:13:37,240
If I were in your situation,

226
00:13:38,210 --> 00:13:39,670
I probably wouldn't have been able to hold on.

227
00:13:39,680 --> 00:13:41,190
Don't underestimate yourself like that.

228
00:13:42,330 --> 00:13:44,290
People don't know their limits

229
00:13:45,030 --> 00:13:47,430
until they face the most dangerous moments.

230
00:13:48,710 --> 00:13:49,710
Maybe it's because

231
00:13:49,710 --> 00:13:51,790
I grew up in a comfortable environment.

232
00:13:52,790 --> 00:13:53,740
I can't imagine it.

233
00:13:54,030 --> 00:13:54,830
Comfortable?

234
00:13:55,710 --> 00:13:56,870
I always thought

235
00:13:56,890 --> 00:13:58,530
that royal family members like you

236
00:13:58,550 --> 00:14:00,190
grew up in the midst of storms

237
00:14:00,220 --> 00:14:01,170
and struggles.

238
00:14:01,540 --> 00:14:02,810
I guess I've been relatively lucky.

239
00:14:03,100 --> 00:14:04,380
Because of my personality, maybe.

240
00:14:05,780 --> 00:14:08,370
I don't push too hard or fight for anything,

241
00:14:09,160 --> 00:14:11,390
so my brother took care of me in every way.

242
00:14:11,950 --> 00:14:14,140
So I didn't get involved in those struggles.

243
00:14:14,170 --> 00:14:15,260
That means

244
00:14:15,290 --> 00:14:16,860
you and your brother have a great relationship.

245
00:14:21,280 --> 00:14:22,790
Actually, as we grew up,

246
00:14:23,920 --> 00:14:25,370
our relationship

247
00:14:28,390 --> 00:14:29,360
became a lot more distant.

248
00:14:31,310 --> 00:14:33,520
I even started to sense his defensiveness toward me.

249
00:14:35,290 --> 00:14:37,990
That's inevitable in royal families.

250
00:14:43,530 --> 00:14:44,400
What's wrong?

251
00:14:47,560 --> 00:14:48,710
I'm bleeding.

252
00:14:57,410 --> 00:14:59,900
You need someone to suck out the blood for you?

253
00:14:59,930 --> 00:15:00,800
I'll do it.

254
00:15:01,380 --> 00:15:03,800
It's fine. Just a minor injury.

255
00:15:08,950 --> 00:15:09,970
Hey, hey, Gao Yin,

256
00:15:10,290 --> 00:15:11,860
you, you take a look at him.

257
00:15:13,390 --> 00:15:15,010
Didn't he say it's fine?

258
00:15:15,040 --> 00:15:16,210
Why apply medicine then?

259
00:15:16,270 --> 00:15:18,280
You really do play favorites, huh?

260
00:15:18,490 --> 00:15:20,920
Wang Yishao was injured earlier too, wasn't he?

261
00:15:21,250 --> 00:15:23,370
Wang Yishao, did you apply any medicine?

262
00:15:28,740 --> 00:15:29,570
Let me see.

263
00:15:33,280 --> 00:15:34,210
You're okay, right?

264
00:15:37,200 --> 00:15:38,640
Since you're fine, get back to work.

265
00:15:45,940 --> 00:15:48,270
A tangled mess, hard to sever and straighten out.

266
00:15:49,150 --> 00:15:50,500
Ah, youth is wonderful.

267
00:15:54,660 --> 00:15:56,090
You old guy.

268
00:15:56,110 --> 00:15:57,870
The lazier you are, the faster you age.

269
00:16:00,350 --> 00:16:02,100
What's that saying again?

270
00:16:03,570 --> 00:16:06,450
"An old man regains the spirit of youth."

271
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:08,990
I admit

272
00:16:09,080 --> 00:16:10,360
I'm pretty old.

273
00:16:10,910 --> 00:16:12,320
But it also proves

274
00:16:12,960 --> 00:16:14,290
that I've experienced a lot.

275
00:16:15,140 --> 00:16:16,640
Kid.

276
00:16:16,750 --> 00:16:18,030
You're the kid here.

277
00:16:27,940 --> 00:16:30,060
All you talk about is nonsense.

278
00:16:30,200 --> 00:16:32,190
I'm telling you, I'm running out of patience.

279
00:16:32,310 --> 00:16:33,400
If you don't start talking,

280
00:16:33,560 --> 00:16:34,600
I'll kill you.

281
00:16:34,800 --> 00:16:36,220
I already told you.

282
00:16:36,390 --> 00:16:38,170
Our boss left a long time ago.

283
00:16:38,230 --> 00:16:39,440
But each of you said something different.

284
00:16:39,490 --> 00:16:40,760
